# EmailJS Configuration for Contact Form
# 
# Setup Instructions:
# 1. Go to https://www.emailjs.com and create a FREE account
# 2. Add an Email Service:
#    - Click "Email Services" in the left menu
#    - Click "Add Service"
#    - Select your email provider (Gmail, Outlook, etc.)
#    - Follow the provider's connection steps
#    - Save and copy the SERVICE ID
#
# 3. Create an Email Template:
#    - Click "Email Templates" in the left menu
#    - Click "Create New Template"
#    - Use template variables: {{from_name}}, {{from_email}}, {{message}}, {{to_name}}
#    - Add a subject line
#    - Save and copy the TEMPLATE ID
#
# 4. Get Your Public API Key:
#    - Click your profile icon → "Account"
#    - Go to "API Keys" section
#    - Copy your Public Key (starts with "public_")
#
# 5. Copy this file to .env and fill in your credentials:
#    cp .env.example .env

VITE_EMAILJS_SERVICE_ID=your_service_id_here
VITE_EMAILJS_TEMPLATE_ID=your_template_id_here
VITE_EMAILJS_PUBLIC_KEY=your_public_key_here
